This paper is about learning interpretable classifiers, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on multiclass classification using probabilistic rule lists and the minimum description length (MDL) principle. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also involves optimization and model selection, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
